author: CBS News
title: First U.S. virus death came weeks before previously thought
description: Santa Clara County, California officials say someone succumbed there on February 6; it was thought a Washington state death in late February was first in U.S.
content:
Two people who died in California in early and mid-February were confirmed Tuesday as coronavirus cases. The first of those deaths came weeks before what was thought to be the first COVID-19 fatality in the United States.
